claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: Page layout showing the table of contents for an MMWR report, text describing CDC adoption of ACIP recommendations, and lists of editorial and production staff members. does not support the claim because the image contains only administrative details and no data or statements comparing antibody responses between higher-dose recombinant flu vaccines and egg-based standard-dose vaccines Note: The image is clear and legible; no relevant immunogenicity or comparative vaccine data are present
